# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# herocast-web — CLIENT build-time vars (Vite import.meta.env)
#
# These differ from .dev.vars: Vite inlines VITE_*-prefixed vars into the CLIENT
# bundle at BUILD time. They are NOT worker-runtime secrets and are NOT read from
# .dev.vars. They're public by design (the anon key is already client-exposed).
#
# LOCAL DEV:  copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
#             `vite dev` / `pnpm build` pick up .env.local automatically.
#
# PRODUCTION: there is no `wrangler secret put` for these — they must be present at
#             BUILD time. Pass them when you build:
#               VITE_SUPABASE_URL=... VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=... pnpm build
#             then `wrangler deploy`. (A `wrangler secret put VITE_*` would land in the
#             worker runtime env, which the already-built client bundle never reads.)
#
# Used by the browser Supabase client (src/lib/supabase/client.ts), which lands in
# Phase 2. Phase 1 does not call it, so these are optional until then.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key
